Date: 23 Aug 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Japan Times 22 Aug 2001 [edited
<http://www.japantimes.co.jp/cgi-bin/getarticle.pl5?nn20010822b4.htm>

NARITA, Chiba Pref. (Kyodo): A man from Saitama Prefecture was found [to
be infected with cholera after returning [on Saturday from Thailand,
health ministry officials at Narita airport said [on Tuesday. The man is
in his 20s and appears to be recovering from the disease, which was
detected during a medical examination at the airport clinic, the officials
from the Health, Labor and Welfare Ministry said.
According to their report, the man visited Bangkok and Phuket Island in
Thailand from 11-18 Aug 2001. He began to suffer diarrhea shortly before
leaving for Japan and [was examined upon arrival at Narita. [This is the
first time this year that cholera has been diagnosed in a passenger
arriving at Narita.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[As mentioned in other ProMED-mail posts, Thailand does not report to the
World Health Organization that it has endemic cholera. Travellers to
Thailand should beware and take the proper precautions - Mod.JW
